<DOC><DOCNO> AP881222-0072 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-12-22-88 0902EST</FILEID><FIRST>r i PM-Israel     12-22 0337</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Israel,0349</SECOND><HEAD>Soldier Dies Of Wounds, 13 Arabs Wounded</HEAD><BYLINE>By RONI RABIN</BYLINE><BYLINE>Associated Press Writer</BYLINE><DATELINE>JERUSALEM (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   An Israeli soldier who was critically injuredwhen he tried to rescue a woman from a passenger bus that wasfirebombed in the West Bank died today in a London hospital, thearmy said.   Also today, troops shot and wounded 13 Palestinians in sporadicclashes in the occupied territories, Arab hospital officials andreporters said.   Military spokesmen said they could not immediately confirm thecasualties in today's violence and were checking the reports.   The soldier's death raised to 14 the number of Israelis who havedied in the yearlong Palestinian revolt against Israeli occupationof the West Bank and Gaza Strip. At least 333 Palestinians have died.   The army identified the soldier as 19-year-old David Deloroza ofJerusalem. He was transferred to a London hospital for an operationto replace his heart and lungs, which were severely damaged fromsmoke inhalation during the firebomb attack near the city of Jericho.   Palestinian guerrillas hurled the bombs at the Israeli bus onOct. 31. Deloroza tried to save Rachel Weiss, an Israeli woman whorefused to leave the burning bus without her children. She and thethree children burned to death.   In Bethlehem, activists belonging to a Palestinian Communistfaction today painted slogans on the walls in red warning Christiansto abide by a general strike called for Christmas Eve.   ``Remain home on Dec. 24,'' one slogan read.   ``No Christmas celebrations .... Only prayers,'' said another.   In the West Bank's largest city of Nablus, Palestinian protesterstook to the streets after a curfew was lifted early today. Fivepeople were wounded in clashes with troops, including a 42-year-oldwoman shot in the arm, local reporters and hospital officials said.   In the occupied Gaza Strip, seven Palestinians were shot andwounded, including a 9-year-old boy shot in the abdomen, Arabdoctors said.   Also today, one man was shot and wounded in the southern WestBank city of Hebron, hospital officials said.</TEXT></DOC>